                <head>No. 1040.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Winchester</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 11, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 137.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 212, of the 21st ultimo,
                    reporting your action under my instruction No. 130 of the 22d of March last to
                    you, relative to measures for preventing the emigration to this country from
                    Switzerland of persons who intend to violate the laws of the United States by
                    entering into polygamous relations, has been received. Your course is approved
                    by the Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
